From 2c7f179007666a27e2f2ef1da9c7074b7895322b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Shwetha G K <kshwetha@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 30 Jun 2025 16:03:24 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAAM:PROTOCOL: hostapd: Save TTLM configs received from
 cli and send it to driver for advertisement

The hostapd_cli command set_advertised_ttlm gets all the TTLM configs to
be advertised in the TTLM IE. Validate the configs received and then call
the driver_ops to send the configs through the NL command if the AP is
operating in beacon_offload mode, i.e. the TTLM IE in the beacon is
managed by the firmware. The configs to be advertised after the mapping
switch time is stored in 'upcoming_ttlm'. Upon mapping switch time expiry,
copy the cofigs of upcoming_ttlm to established_ttlm and clear the
upcoming_ttlm. The TTLM in the established_ttlm is then advertised for a
duration equal to the expected_duration value set through the cli command.

Also, add a wiphy feature flag to denote if driver supports offload of
TTLM element management in beacon.

Signed-off-by: Shwetha G K <kshwetha@qti.qualcomm.com>
Signed-off-by: Amith A <amitajit@qti.qualcomm.com>
